      <originalsloc id="aspace_c8aef393804d4fe00174fd6a1f73e501">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Natural Science Manuscripts Collection (MS: 583).   This collection is an artificial collection of the papers of Yale faculty members and other individuals active in the academic fields of astronomy, biology, botany, geology, mathematics, physics, agriculture, chemistry, and zoology.   The papers of inventors are also included.</p>
         <p>HM 188 only consists of: A Journal which includes lectures on chemistry delivered at the University of North Carolina, 1824 - from box 8 folder 288a</p>  
